definition.value: The conjugate base of 3,5-dibromo-4-hydroxybenzonitrile; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of thiomorpholine-3-carboxylic acid arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-asparagine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of dolichyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dicarboxylate anion of 4,5-dihydroxyphthalic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is a trianion arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and diphosphate OH groups of UDP-alpha-D-glucuronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of IMP; major species at pH 7.3.

Dicarboxylate anion of 2-methylideneglutaric acid; major species at pH 7.3.

Zwitterionic form of homocysteine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

Conjugate base of (3Z,5S)-3-(1-hydroxyethylidene)-5-{[4-(3-methylbut-2-en-1-yl)-1H-indol-3-yl]methyl}pyrrolidine-2,4-dione arising from deprotonation of the enolic hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
